    "The experimental implementation and the analysis protocol are shown in Extended Data Fig. 9a, b, and the IRB results are shown in Extended Data Fig.",
    "We then fit the randomized benchmarking decay curve to the formula 38, 41",
    "from which 1 - 0.5b gives the Clifford fidelity in single-qubit randomized benchmarking, and 1 - 0.75b gives the Clifford fidelity in two-qubit randomized benchmarking.",
    "The term c represents the decay exponent and reflects the error Markovianity; a is subjected to the readout fidelity and d is close to 0.5.",
    "From the two-qubit IRB decays, we first obtain an IRB fidelity 50 of 99.8 ± 0.2% at T = 0.1 K and 97.7 ± 1.5% at T = 1 K for the DCZ gate."
